Äì The superior WordPress slider plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/r08UunU4PbE/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:80:"https://updraftplus.com/metaslider-the-superior-wordpress-slider-plugin/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 18 Jul 2019 14:56:09 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"MetaSlider";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"MetaSlider update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"https://updraftplus.com/?p=412690";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:732:"<p>Whether you run a company as big as Apple or Amazon, or just run your own blog as a freelancer &#8211; slideshows are an increasingly popular way to showcase the photos or message you want people to see first when &#8230; <a href="https://updraftplus.com/metaslider-the-superior-wordpress-slider-plugin/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com/metaslider-the-superior-wordpress-slider-plugin/">MetaSlider &#8211; The superior WordPress slider plugin</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href="http://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"wmullins";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12759:"<p><a href="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/MetaSlider-log.png"><img class=" wp-image-412692 aligncenter" src="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/MetaSlider-log.png" alt="" width="478" height="131" srcset="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/MetaSlider-log.png 576w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/MetaSlider-log-300x82.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/MetaSlider-log-510x140.png 510w" sizes="(max-width: 478px) 100vw, 478px" /></a></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Whether you run a company as big as Apple or Amazon, or just run your own blog as a freelancer &#8211; slideshows are an increasingly popular way to showcase the photos or message you want people to see first when they visit your website.¬†</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Choosing the best WordPress slider plugin is an important crucial element of the design and overall look of your website, as it is one of the first things a visitor will see. A slick and stylish display of your images or videos could be the difference between an initial positive or negative interaction.¬†</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The <a href="https://www.metaslider.com/">MetaSlider</a> plugin has gained huge popularity amongst the WordPress community by assisting users in creating incredibly high quality sliders. MetaSlider allows you to elect from multiple transition effects and choose different slider styles to add greater versatility to your website.¬†</span></p>\n<p><b>About MetaSlider</b></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Both the </span><a href="https://en-gb.wordpress.org/plugins/ml-slider/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Free</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and </span><a href="https://www.metaslider.com/upgrade/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Premium</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> versions of the MetaSlider plugin are available for users to download today. Creating SEO-optimized slideshows is easy and straightforward, as you just select the images/video from your WordPress Media Library, before dragging and dropping them into your slider. The plugin can even be used with template tags and shortcodes in your WordPress site.</span></p>\n<p><b>Features Of MetaSlider</b></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Although it is very easy to use, MetaSlider packs in a load of advanced features which can cater to all ranges of ability, ranging from an amateur to a professional. Whether you are a professional web designer creating an innovative and complex website for a client, or simply want to put together your first site and make a good impression &#8211; MetaSlider will have your back at all times with the following cutting edge features:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Image Slider ‚Äì Directly adds your chosen images to your slideshows. The most popular basic slider type &#8211; available in the free version of MetaSlider plugin. You can also add captions, adjust the display settings of the slider and setup the SEO field. The slider can also be linked to a URL of your choice for added functionality. If you decide to upgrade to MetaSlider Pro, you can also alter the look of the slider‚Äôs arrows, navigation options and captions. Image Slider is also available in Responsive Slides, Flex Slider, Nivo Slider and Coin Slider.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div id="attachment_412693" style="width: 842px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-66.jpg"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-412693" class="wp-image-412693" src="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-66.jpg" alt="" width="832" height="465" srcset="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-66.jpg 1418w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-66-300x168.jpg 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-66-768x429.jpg 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-66-1024x573.jpg 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-66-1080x604.jpg 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-66-510x285.jpg 510w" sizes="(max-width: 832px) 100vw, 832px" /></a><p id="caption-attachment-412693" class="wp-caption-text">How the setup of image slider appears in the MetaSlider plugin</p></div>\n<ul>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Animated Layer Slider ‚Äì This feature is available with MetaSlider Pro and allows users to create visually stunning CSS3 slideshows by unleashing the full potential of 50 different animation options. It‚Äôs easy to use interface further adds to the overall usability of the plugin. Videos, images, text, html and even shortcodes can also be included, improving additional slider options for users.¬†</span></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Video Slider ‚Äì A video can be added as the slider background. After adding the video, you can also adjust the background colour and padding of each layer to create amazing results. The layer slides included in the MetaSlider Pro pack is also compatible with Responsive Slides and Flex Slider.</span></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Thumbnails ‚Äì This brand-new feature from MetaSlider Pro gives users two different variations of slideshow navigation.¬†</span>\n<ul>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Thumbnail: Displays a static row of thumbnails at the bottom interface of the slideshow. This is compatible with both Nivo Slider and Flex Slider.¬†</span></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Flimstrip: Displays a carousel style output at the bottom region of the slideshow. This is compatible with Flex Slider and is useful if you are dealing with multiple slides.</span></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div id="attachment_412694" style="width: 743px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-67.jpg"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-412694" class="wp-image-412694 size-full" src="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-67.jpg" alt="" width="733" height="476" srcset="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-67.jpg 733w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-67-300x195.jpg 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-67-510x331.jpg 510w" sizes="(max-width: 733px) 100vw, 733px" /></a><p id="caption-attachment-412694" class="wp-caption-text">Just enable thumbnail navigation for existing or new slideshows and choose the height and width of the filmstrip or static style of thumbnails. Thumbnails are compatible with all slide types.</p></div>\n<ul>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Post Feed Slides ‚Äì Show off your content using this popular MetaSlider premium feature. It offers users the ability to add events, latest blog posts and even WooCommerce products. Users can easily control which slides to display, their order of appearance and even restrict posts that fall under certain categories. The caption template can also be customized to show the title, author, excerpt and date tags.¬†</span></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Carousel ‚Äì Display a variety of your newest post by using this free MetaSlider feature. This is especially helpful when you need to show a lot of content in a limited space. Just set the slideshow type to ‚ÄòFlex Slider‚Äô to get all the benefits. Vimeo, YouTube, Layer, Post Feel and Image slides are also compatible with Carousels.¬†</span></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Online Video Slides ‚Äì This MetaSlider Pro feature adds videos to your slideshow by simply adding a Vimeo or YouTube URL to a slide. You can create a slideshow comprising of your favourite videos or even mix and match between different slides to get your preferred result. Opt for the FlexSlider option while working on video slides to access the play/pause functionality of MetaSlider.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Smart Crop ‚Äì Easily resize your slides using this unique feature.¬†</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div id="attachment_412697" style="width: 612px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-69.jpg"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-412697" class="wp-image-412697 size-full" src="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-69.jpg" alt="" width="602" height="373" srcset="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-69.jpg 602w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-69-300x186.jpg 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-69-510x316.jpg 510w" sizes="(max-width: 602px) 100vw, 602px" /></a><p id="caption-attachment-412697" class="wp-caption-text">Add an online video by simply adding the URL</p></div>\n<p><b>Benefits Of MetaSlider</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Able to display a wide variety of content that can help business owners and freelancers display project logos and past client testimonials.</span></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Users are not limited to standard slideshows and can take their pick from many different styles and designs.</span></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Comes fully integrated with the brand new WordPress 3.5 media manager to open up greater possibilities.</span></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Prioritized customer support for Pro users. Get any issues fixed quickly.</span></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Compatible with most WordPress plugins: Events Calendar, WooCommerce and WPML.</span></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Developer friendly plugin that offers users amazing customization possibilities.</span></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Slides can be scheduled to appear within specific dates (Pro only).</span></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Works seamlessly with the Gutenberg WordPress designer.</span></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">11 amazing professional slider themes &#8211; absolutely free of charge.¬†</span></li>\n<li>More than 50 built-in CSS3 transitions (Pro version).</li>\n</ul>\n<div id="attachment_412698" style="width: 896px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-70.jpg"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-412698" class="wp-image-412698" src="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-70.jpg" alt="" width="886" height="566" srcset="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-70.jpg 1269w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-70-300x192.jpg 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-70-768x491.jpg 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-70-1024x654.jpg 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-70-1080x690.jpg 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/New-Project-70-510x326.jpg 510w" sizes="(max-width: 886px) 100vw, 886px" /></a><p id="caption-attachment-412698" class="wp-caption-text">All the different themes available in MetaSlider</p></div>\n<p><b>Summing up MetaSlider</b></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="https://www.metaslider.com/">MetaSlider</a> is an easy to use and powerful tool that can help anyone with a WordPress site display lots of information directly to users, without the requirement of manual scrolling. This can potentially be used as an amazing marketing tool tool by just about anyone. By using MetaSlider, you can display lots of your most important content to users, which can potentially lead to greater conversions in the future; making it ideal for sites that have a high bounce rate.</span></p>\n<p><a href="https://techigem.com/">Jennifer S. Colby</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com/metaslider-the-superior-wordpress-slider-plugin/">MetaSlider &#8211; The superior WordPress slider plugin</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href="http://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:77:"https://updraftplus.com/metaslider-the-superior-wordpress-slider-plugin/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:72:"https://updraftplus.com/metaslider-the-superior-wordpress-slider-plugin/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:70:"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:143:"UpdraftPlus announces new feature to spin out empty WP installs with a couple of clicks!  Perfect for testing new plugins, themes or designs‚Ä¶";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/-qQuJvUN0zc/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"https://updraftplus.com/updraftclone-gets-a-new-dashboard-update/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 04 Jul 2019 10:55:29 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"UpdraftClone";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Clone";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Clone Update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"https://updraftplus.com/?p=407321";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:869:"<p>Our revolutionary UpdraftClone feature (&#8220;copy &#38; paste your WordPress site&#8221;) has proven a massive success since the September launch. UpdraftClone allows users to clone your site to the cloud in a couple of clicks, without having to arrange new hosting.¬†¬† &#8230; <a href="https://updraftplus.com/updraftclone-gets-a-new-dashboard-update/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com/updraftclone-gets-a-new-dashboard-update/">UpdraftPlus announces new feature to spin out empty WP installs with a couple of clicks!  Perfect for testing new plugins, themes or designs&#8230;</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href="http://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"wmullins";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5235:"<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Our revolutionary <a href="https://updraftplus.com/updraftclone/">UpdraftClone</a> feature (&#8220;copy &amp; paste your WordPress site&#8221;) has proven a massive success since the September launch. UpdraftClone</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> allows users to clone your site to the cloud in a couple of clicks, without having to arrange new hosting.¬†¬†</span></p>\n<p>But today we announce you can now spin out <strong>Blank</strong> <strong>WordPress Installs</strong> with just a couple of clicks.</p>\n<p>This new UpdraftClone feature allows you to boot empty WordPress installs from the <a href="https://updraftplus.com/my-account/clones/">UpdraftPlus.com clone dashboard</a> directly.¬† You can now easily create an empty WordPress install on which you can test new themes/plugins/updates without the need to clone your existing site.</p>\n<p>This new feature uses the same Clone token system as UpdraftClone, so you can now generate a new blank WP install quickly and easily without even need to enter credit card details. It‚Äôs so quick and easy and¬†you can simply throw the clone away again once you‚Äôre done testing ‚Äì you can always spin out another one when you need it.</p>\n<p><strong>How it works.</strong></p>\n<p><a href="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-407322 aligncenter" src="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0.png" alt="" width="1240" height="544" srcset="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0.png 1240w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-300x132.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-768x337.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-1024x449.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-1080x474.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-510x224.png 510w" sizes="(max-width: 1240px) 100vw, 1240px" /></a></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once you have created an Empty Install, you now have a &#8216;Quick actions&#8217; option that allows you to easily delete, reboot or access the SSH login of the Clone without having to go through multiple sub-menu options.¬†</span></p>\n<p><a href="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-1.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-407323 aligncenter" src="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-1.png" alt="" width="917" height="416" srcset="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-1.png 917w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-1-300x136.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-1-768x348.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-1-510x231.png 510w" sizes="(max-width: 917px) 100vw, 917px" /></a></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Within each individual Empty Install or Clone, you can now click ‚ÄúManage‚Äù and view a range of easy to use &#8216;actions&#8217; where you can directly access the Database login, SSH access, PHP info, change the PHP version, reboot the clone and show SFTP access credential.¬†</span></p>\n<p><a href="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-2.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-407324 aligncenter" src="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-2.png" alt="" width="903" height="577" srcset="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-2.png 903w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-2-300x192.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-2-768x491.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/pasted-image-0-2-510x326.png 510w" sizes="(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px" /></a></p>\n<p>This service is primarily designed for testing things out on a temporary throw-away site rather than long term hosting, simply because you can‚Äôt choose your own domain (yet).¬†But should you wish to keep the site¬†you created from the &#8216;Blank Install&#8217;, you can use UpdraftPlus Migrator feature to migrate it to any live site, on any domain, with any host you like.</p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">We are sure this new update to the UpdraftClone dashboard and features will provide a useful service for those wanting to test things out quickly.¬†¬†</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you&#8217;re a customer, you can sign into your UpdraftPlus.com account and check out the changes today on your <a href="https://updraftplus.com/my-account/clones/">UpdraftPlus.com clone dashboard.</a></span></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com/updraftclone-gets-a-new-dashboard-update/">UpdraftPlus announces new feature to spin out empty WP installs with a couple of clicks!  Perfect for testing new plugins, themes or designs&#8230;</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href="http://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://updraftplus.com/updraftclone-gets-a-new-dashboard-update/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"https://updraftplus.com/updraftclone-gets-a-new-dashboard-update/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:63:"\n		\n		\n				\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n				\n								\n										";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:4:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:43:"How to use Advanced Custom Fields with WPML";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/X47NI63xvG0/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 26 Jun 2019 13:27:53 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"Other WordPress news";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"Tips and tricks";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:22:"Advanced Custom Fields";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Blog";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"wordpress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"WPML";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"https://updraftplus.com/?p=404340";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:766:"<p>The Advanced Custom Fields and WPML plugins have both proven to be very popular with WordPress users. At the time of publishing this article, the WordPress plugin repository shows 1+ million active installation for the &#8216;Advanced Custom Fields&#8217; plugin. For &#8230; <a href="https://updraftplus.com/how-to-use-advanced-custom-fields-with-wpml/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com/how-to-use-advanced-custom-fields-with-wpml/">How to use Advanced Custom Fields with WPML</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href="http://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"wmullins";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12491:"<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The</span><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/advanced-custom-fields"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Advanced Custom Fields</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and</span><a href="https://wpml.org"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">WPML</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> plugins have both proven to be very popular with WordPress users. At the time of publishing this article, the WordPress plugin repository shows 1+ million active installation for the &#8216;Advanced Custom Fields&#8217; plugin. For such a popular plugin, it&#8217;s seems like WPML would make it a priority to provide a compatibility bridge for users &#8211; and now they have!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">With Advanced Custom Fields (ACF) users can easily add meta box(es) to a post, page, custom post type and even categories. Meta boxes can be incredibly useful when you want to show additional information regarding the resource.¬†</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you are building a multilingual website in WordPress, you obviously want these ACF meta boxes to work efficiently on the translated versions of your post, page, etc. In this article, we show you the steps on how to configure and use ACF with WPML, as using both plugins together makes for a great experience as it integrates with the website seamlessly.</span></p>\n<p><b>Installation</b></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once you have decided on building a multilingual website with ACF, grab a copy of the following plugins and install (but don‚Äôt activate) them on your WordPress dashboard.¬†</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/advanced-custom-fields"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Advanced Custom Fields</span></a></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="https://wpml.org"><span style="font-weight: 400;">WPML</span></a></li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Advanced Custom Fields Multilingual</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The ‚ÄòAdvanced Custom Fields Multilingual‚Äô plugin can be found in the</span><a href="https://wpml.org/account/downloads"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">download section of your WPML account page</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. After you have installed all 3 plugins, activate the ACF and WPML plugins. Keep the ACF Multilingual plugin deactivated as you will need to complete setting up WPML first.</span></p>\n<p><b>WPML setup on the WordPress dashboard</b></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">After activating the WPML plugin you will see a notice on top of the page that asks you to &#8216;Configure WPML&#8217;.</span></p>\n<p><a href="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-404357" src="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1.png" alt="" width="882" height="166" srcset="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1.png 882w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1-300x56.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1-768x145.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1-510x96.png 510w" sizes="(max-width: 882px) 100vw, 882px" /></a></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Press this button and it will redirect you to the WPML setup page. Here you will find the default option is set to the language you selected at the time of WordPress installation.¬†</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For this example, it is set to &#8216;English&#8217;.</span></p>\n<p><a href="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/2.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-404358" src="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/2.png" alt="" width="1600" height="444" srcset="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/2.png 1600w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/2-300x83.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/2-768x213.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/2-1024x284.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/2-1080x300.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/2-510x142.png 510w" sizes="(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px" /></a></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Press &#8216;Next&#8217; once done.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In step 2, you can select your secondary language. A user can select more than one option if they intend to display their website in multiple languages. For this example, let&#8217;s say you just wanted French as a secondary language. You would tick that option from the list and press ‚ÄòNext‚Äô.</span></p>\n<p><a href="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/3.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-404359" src="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/3.png" alt="" width="1456" height="552" srcset="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/3.png 1456w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/3-300x114.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/3-768x291.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/3-1024x388.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/3-1080x409.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/3-510x193.png 510w" sizes="(max-width: 1456px) 100vw, 1456px" /></a></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For the third step, select the default setting and press ‚ÄòNext‚Äô.¬†</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Complete the fourth step as per the plugin instruction.¬†</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For the final step, add your WPML registration key and press the &#8216;Register&#8217; button to finish the setup.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">After finishing the setup, you will be redirected to the WPML setting page. Scroll down to the &#8216;Language URL format&#8217; section and choose the URL format you want.¬†</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">We recommend choosing the first option &#8211; &#8216;Different languages in directories&#8217;, which generates SEO-friendly URLs for translated pages.</span></p>\n<p><a href="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/4.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-404360" src="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/4.png" alt="" width="1472" height="356" srcset="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/4.png 1472w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/4-300x73.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/4-768x186.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/4-1024x248.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/4-1080x261.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/4-510x123.png 510w" sizes="(max-width: 1472px) 100vw, 1472px" /></a></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Now go to your plugin page and activate the &#8216;Advanced Custom Fields Multilingual&#8217; plugin. This plugin does not have any settings to configure and should work quietly in the background.</span></p>\n<p><b>Advanced Custom Fields with WPML</b></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">When using Advanced Custom Fields (ACF) with WPML, you will want to show the same ACF meta boxes for both the primary and secondary languages. By doing this, it ensures a consistent functionality for both the backend and frontend. To do this, you just need to put translated content in the secondary language.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">We will create a meta box for the primary language (English for this example), which causes the meta box to appear on the assigned page.¬†</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">After translating this page in our secondary language, the same meta box should now appear on the translated version of our page.¬†</span></p>\n<p><b>Let&#8217;s take a look at this whole process in action‚Ä¶..</b></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">First, create a page called &#8216;About Us&#8217; and publish this page.¬†</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Next, head over to the &#8216;Custom Fields&#8217; menu and add one meta box for the &#8216;About Us&#8217; page.</span></p>\n<p><a href="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/5.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-404361" src="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/5.png" alt="" width="1304" height="478" srcset="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/5.png 1304w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/5-300x110.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/5-768x282.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/5-1024x375.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/5-1080x396.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/5-510x187.png 510w" sizes="(max-width: 1304px) 100vw, 1304px" /></a></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Now go to the edit screen of the &#8216;About Us&#8217; page, where this meta box should appear. Add some content in the &#8216;Our Aim&#8217; field.</span></p>\n<p><a href="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/6.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-404362" src="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/6.png" alt="" width="1318" height="560" srcset="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/6.png 1318w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/6-300x127.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/6-768x326.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/6-1024x435.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/6-1080x459.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/6-510x217.png 510w" sizes="(max-width: 1318px) 100vw, 1318px" /></a></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Next, you need to create the French version of this page. To do this press the &#8216;+&#8217; icon under the &#8216;Translate&#8217; column. This box is on right side of your edit screen.</span></p>\n<p><a href="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/7.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-404367" src="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/7.png" alt="" width="314" height="290" srcset="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/7.png 314w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/7-300x277.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 314px) 100vw, 314px" /></a></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You will now be redirected to the new page. Add the page title &#8216;About Us&#8217; in French and publish the page. Reload the page and you should see your ACF meta box and also see original content of your primary language in textual format. You can now add a French translation for this content.</span></p>\n<p><a href="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/8.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-404368" src="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/8.png" alt="" width="1332" height="664" srcset="https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/8.png 1332w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/8-300x150.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/8-768x383.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/8-1024x510.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/8-1080x538.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/8-510x254.png 510w" sizes="(max-width: 1332px) 100vw, 1332px" /></a></p>\n<p><b>Note:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> The steps shown in this tutorial are performed on a fresh WordPress installation. If you are trying these steps on your existing site, then you might get a different result than is shown in this blog.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">That&#8217;s it! You are now all set with the Advanced Custom Fields setup, with WPML functionality.¬†</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you have any comments or questions, we would like to hear your thoughts in the comment section below.</span></p>\n<p>By Sajid Sayyad</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com/how-to-use-advanced-custom-fields-with-wpml/">How to use Advanced Custom Fields with WPML</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href="http://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:68:"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-use-advanced-custom-fields-with-wpml/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";a:2:{s:12:"updatePeriod";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"\n	hourly	";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:15:"updateFrequency";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"\n	1	";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:1:{s:4:"link";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"rel";s:4:"self";s:4:"type";s:19:"application/rss+xml";s:4:"href";s:39:"http://feeds.feedburner.com/UpdraftPlus";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:2:{s:3:"rel"